# PlotOps

Git-oriented CRM (Jira/Linear clone) with GitHub integration. Portfolio project targeting Middle-level frontend skills.

## Tech Stack (current)

- **Frontend:** Vite, React 19, TanStack Router, TanStack Query, Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui, i18next
- **Architecture:** Feature-Sliced Design — `src/app`, `src/routes`, `src/features`, `src/shared`
- **State:** TanStack Query (server/async), Zustand (UI — when needed)
- **Backend:** Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Realtime, Storage, Edge Functions)
- **Env vars:** `VITE_SUPABASE_URL`, `VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`

## Full Spec

Read `docs/SPEC.md` before implementing major features. For the latest version, fetch Notion page **"CRM system with Github integration"**.

**Progress:** current implementation status lives in `docs/SPEC.md` → Progress. After completing a roadmap item or stage, update that section in the same PR/commit.

## Core Features (roadmap)

1. **Git Kanban** — tasks linked to branches; drag-and-drop updates status; branch name generator (`feature/TASK-123-login-page`)
2. **In-app Git** — PR list, commit history, code diff viewer (no redirect to GitHub)
3. **CI/CD Dashboard** — build status per branch, streaming build logs
4. **Command Palette** — `Ctrl+K` / `Cmd+K` via `cmdk`
5. **Guest Mode** — demo without GitHub OAuth; pre-seeded projects, tasks, fake diffs and CI logs

## Database (Supabase)

Tables: `profiles`, `projects`, `tasks`, `activity_log`. Enable **RLS** from day one — users see only their projects/tasks.

### Supabase project (PlotOps only)

- **Remote project ref:** parse from `.env` → `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` host (`https://<ref>.supabase.co`). Current PlotOps ref: `ijcelrdcygzyzhcijkhe`.
- **Other Supabase projects** (e.g. bailyq / `mcuvozjlvifdhihqwosh`) belong to a different app — **never** run migrations or MCP SQL against them from this repo unless the user explicitly names that project.
- **MCP:** pass `project_id` = PlotOps ref from `.env` on every Supabase MCP call. Do **not** use `list_projects()[0]` or any default. If MCP returns permission denied for PlotOps, stop and tell the user to re-auth MCP or use CLI — do not fall back to another project.
- **CLI (preferred for schema):** `npm run db:push` after `npx supabase login` and `npm run db:link` (one-time). Migrations live in `supabase/migrations/`.
- **New migrations:** `npx supabase migration new <name>` — never invent filenames.

## Key Patterns

- TanStack Query hooks for Supabase (not raw `useEffect`); optimistic updates on kanban drag-drop
- Supabase Realtime subscription on `tasks` for live board sync
- SQL triggers for `activity_log` on status changes
- GitHub webhooks → Supabase Edge Function → sync PR merge to task `DONE`

## UI Components (shadcn/ui)

**Prefer shadcn/ui over raw HTML** — use existing primitives from `@/shared/shadcn/ui` instead of hand-rolling `<button>`, `<input>`, `<dialog>`, cards, dropdowns, etc.

- **Import path:** `@/shared/shadcn/ui/<component>` (see `components.json` aliases)
- **Before writing UI:** check `src/shared/shadcn/ui/` — reuse what's already installed
- **Missing component:** add via `npm run shadcn:add -- <name>` (e.g. `input`, `dialog`, `card`) — auto-updates `src/shared/shadcn/index.tsx`; or `npm run shadcn:exports` to regenerate the barrel after manual adds
- **Compose, don't reinvent:** build feature UI by composing shadcn primitives + Tailwind; raw HTML only when no suitable primitive exists or the markup is trivially structural (`<div>`, `<section>`, layout wrappers)
- **Icons:** `lucide-react` (project default per `components.json`)

## Design

Dark, strict, Linear/Neobrutalism-inspired: sharp borders, monospace for git elements, neon accents on build statuses (green success, red failure). No gratuitous gradients.

## Git commits

**Never add Cursor attribution to commits or PRs.** Do not append `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Made-with: Cursor`, `--trailer`, or any similar AI/tool footer to commit messages. Use only the subject and body you write (`git commit -m "…"` or `-F` file). If a hook or environment still injects attribution, amend the message to remove it before finishing — do not leave it in history.

When the user asks for a commit, follow their commit message only; never add co-author or attribution lines on your own.
